HEADWORD: Winter-proud
<hw>Win"ter-proud`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having too rank
or forward a growth for winter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When either corn is <qex>winter-proud</qex>, or other plants put
forth and bud too early.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Winter-rig</ent>⟦br⟧
